"With cries and clamours his request renew. The modest queen awhile, with down-cast eyes, Ponder'd the speech, then briefly thus replies : Â¢ Trojans ! dismiss your fears: my cruel fate, And doubts attending an unsettled state, Force me to guard my coast from foreign foes. Wiho has not heard the story of your woes, The name and fortune of your native place, The fame and valour of the Phrygian race? We Tyrians are not so devoid of sense,"